:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Dovy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2567:"<p class="p1"><span class="s1">You know youâ€™ve hit a home run when your business&#8217;s activity doubles within two months and support issues are reduce by nearly 1/3.Â  Thatâ€™s what has happened with Redux since we launched the <a title="Redux Generator" href="http://build.stg.redux.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Redux Builder</a>.</span></p>
<p class="p1">In early March, I conceived the idea to design a site that would auto-generate a Redux<br />
build.Â  Actually, I wanted to build a fully-fledged panel builder like Option Tree, but with the sheer amount of options available with Redux, the time required would be intense&#8230;and then some.Â  Instead, I considered building a boilerplate generator for themes.Â  And what better theme than the ever powerful <a title="_s" href="http://underscores.me" target="_blank" rel="noopener">_s</a> by <a title="Automattic" href="http://automattic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Automattic</a>?Â  I found their generator code and went to town, including a TGM integration, and a slew of Redux arguments.</p>
<p class="p1">Today, I am extremely pleased to announce we took the project it a step further.Â  We organized the arguments, gave descriptions, and links for each to our docs site.Â  We also made it so one could easily export to an admin folder instead of a theme.Â  This comes in handy for use in existing products and/or plugins.Â  Lastly, we&#8217;ve now made every Redux field completely independent.Â  As a result, you can generate a custom build of Redux Framework with your export!</p>
<p class="p1">Â Yes, you read that correctly!Â  You can make a custom Redux Framework build!Â  Since one of the biggest complaints about Redux has been its size, weighing in at 6mb for all (34+) fields, the Framework tends to be quite heavy.Â  Now, that&#8217;s a thing of the past.</p>
<p class="p1">Weâ€™re really excited about the new version of the Redux Builder.Â  Major props to team member @kprovance for making Redux fields completely modular.</p>
<p>If you havenâ€™t tried the builder, you SHOULD.Â  Itâ€™s free.Â  It will save you time.Â  Oh, and itâ€™s so very choice.</p>
<h3 class="p1" style="text-align: center;"><a title="Redux Generator" href="http://build.stg.redux.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">http://build.stg.redux.io</a></h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1">Just a gentle reminder, Redux lives by donations and our extensions.Â  So if you like the generator, please consider donating a small amount to the project.Â  You support us, and we&#8217;ll keep making cool things.</p>
